Company Overview of Rothschild Asset Management Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Rothschild Asset Management Inc. is a privately owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to individuals. It also caters to high net worth individuals, pension and profit sharing plans, pooled investment vehicles, corporations, state or municipal government entities, proprietary accounts, endowments, foundations, healthcare organizations, public pension funds, and Taft-Hartley plans. The firm manages separate client-focused equity and balanced portfolios. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. The firm primarily invests in value and growth stocks of small cap, mid cap, and large cap companies. For the fixed income portion, it i...
Rothschild Asset Management Inc. is a privately owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to individuals. It also caters to high net worth individuals, pension and profit sharing plans, pooled investment vehicles, corporations, state or municipal government entities, proprietary accounts, endowments, foundations, healthcare organizations, public pension funds, and Taft-Hartley plans. The firm manages separate client-focused equity and balanced portfolios. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. The firm primarily invests in value and growth stocks of small cap, mid cap, and large cap companies. For the fixed income portion, it invests in U.S. Treasury bonds and agency and investment-grade corporate bonds. The firm employs a combination of quantitative and fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach to create its portfolios. It was founded in December 1982 and is based in New York City, New York. Rothschild Asset Management Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Rothschild North America Inc.
