Rothschild Asset Management Inc. Key Developments

APS Asset Management and Rothschild Asset Management Enter into Strategic Alliance
Jul 3 17
APS Asset Management and Rothschild Asset Management Inc. have entered into a strategic alliance. The strategic alliance seeks to strengthen APS' position in the US and Rothschild Asset Management's position in Asia. This alliance also involves general marketing which Rothschild Asset Management will extend to APS in the US. In Asia, APS will extend similar support to Rothschild Asset Management.


CIBC Asset Management Announces Sub Advisor Changes to Imperial U.S. Equity Pool, Renaissance U.S. Equity Private Pool and Renaissance U.S. Equity Value Fund
Nov 26 16
CIBC Asset Management Inc. announced portfolio sub-advisor changes to further strengthen its core investment solutions with the addition of Morgan Stanley Investment Management Inc. (MSIM) and Rothschild Asset Management Inc. on certain mandates effective on or about December 16, 2016, and January 24, 2017, respectively. Imperial U.S. Equity Pool- MSIM and Rothschild Asset Management Inc. have been appointed as portfolio sub-advisors for the Imperial U.S. Equity Pool. These portfolio sub-advisors will join CIBC Asset Management Inc., American Century Investment Management Inc. (American Century), Pzena Investment Management, LLC (Pzena), and Sustainable Growth Advisers, LP (SGA); Renaissance U.S. Equity Private Pool- MSIM and Rothschild Asset Management Inc. have been appointed as portfolio sub-advisors for the Renaissance U.S. Equity Private Pool. These portfolio sub-advisors will join INTECH Investment Management LLC, Pzena and SGA; Renaissance U.S. Equity Value Fund- Rothschild Asset Management Inc. has been appointed portfolio sub-advisor for the Renaissance U.S. Equity Value Fund.


Advisors Asset Management Expands Strategic Partnership with Rothschild Asset Management Inc
Jun 23 16
Advisors Asset Management (AAM) announced that it has entered into an agreement with Rothschild Asset Management Inc. to become the distributor for select separately managed accounts (SMAs), including Rothschild's U.S. Large-Cap Core, U.S. Large-Cap Value and U.S. Balanced strategies. This agreement expands the scope of the existing partnership between AAM and Rothschild. In March, AAM became the sub-advisor for the fixed-income component of Rothschild's U.S.  Balanced SMA strategies, and agreed to perform the administrative and back-office functions for these portfolios. The prior accord also enabled AAM to distribute Rothschild's U.S. Balanced SMAs.  The new agreement will expand AAM's distribution and operations functions to include Rothschild's U.S.  Large-Cap Core and U.S.  Large-Cap Value strategies. Rothschild will continue to serve as investment manager for the two large-cap strategies and the investment advisor to the Balanced strategy with AAM acting as the sub-advisor for the fixed income portion.


